            categories.name AS category_name, categories.slug AS category_slug,

            provinces.name AS province_name,
            (SELECT url FROM pictures WHERE products.product_id = pictures.product_id ORDER BY pictures.picture_id ASC LIMIT 1) AS thumbnail from `products` left join `suppliers` on `suppliers`.`supplier_id` = `products`.`supplier_id` left join `categories` on `categories`.`category_id` = `products`.`category_id` left join `provinces` on `provinces`.`province_id` = `suppliers`.`province_id` where `categories`.`deleted_at` is null and `suppliers`.`deleted_at` is null and `products`.`deleted_at` is null

                        categories.name AS category_name, categories.slug AS category_slug,

SQL : (2018-07-26 02:16:50)update `suppliers` set `introduction` = ?, `updated_at` = ? where `supplier_id` = ?
Binndings : 
<p class="p1"><strong>Our Background</strong></p>
<p class="p2">The Farmers Own initiative was started back in 2013 with Farmers from the Manning Valley in NSW. The brand began with a trial of just eight local stores within the Manning Valley and 12 Sydney stores in NSW. It's success saw the brand expand into VIC, QLD, WA, SA and NT, all the while building direct relationships with Farmers from key provincial areas within these states (Margaret River WA. Otways Regions VIC, Sunshine Coast Hinterland QLD and Barossa Mid North Region SA). In a challenging time for Australian Dairy Farmers, Farmers Own has been a good news story. Check out our packaging to see what our Farmers have to say!</p>
<p class="p1"><strong>Our Deal</strong></p>
<p class="p2">We have direct relationships with our Farmers and not via a processor or a Co-op to ensure they are getting a good deal every time. Our goal is to pay our Farmers a good price for their milk that allows them to continue to produce quality milk. We pick up milk from their farms and transport directly to be processed so we know exactly where the milk comes from that goes into Farmers' Own milk. Our Farmers are engaged in the branding and feel a sense of belonging to the brand because it is their milk that goes into each bottle. We work with our farmers on sustainable and good animal husbandry practices and our farmers and families are proudly active in promoting Farmers' Own branded milk in their communities.</p>
<p class="p1"><strong>Awards we've won!</strong></p>
<p class="p2">Since launching, Farmers&rsquo; Own has gone onto win a bunch of Awards within Australian Dairy and Food Competitions listed below:&nbsp;</p>
<ul class="ul1">
<li class="li2">Gold medal at the 2014 Royal Melbourne Fine Food Awards</li>
<li class="li2">Bronze and silver medals in the 2016 Royal Queensland Food and Wine Show</li>
<li class="li2">Gold and Silver at the 2016 DIIA - Dairy Industry Association of Australia Show</li>
<li class="li2">Silver Medal in 2016 the Perth Royal Dairy Show</li>
<li class="li2">Bronze and Silver in the 2016 Royal Queensland Food and Wine Show</li>
</ul>
2018-07-26 14:16:50

1
<p class="p1">Great for a fish pie, hake&rsquo;s firm, sweet, white meat makes it one of our best fish. It&rsquo;s got a medium flake and a milder flavour than cod.&nbsp;</p>
<p class="p1">Our hake comes from both Cornwall and the Irish/North Seas. From Cornwall it will either be gill or fixed netted and have an MCS rating of 1. When caught in the Irish/North Sea, it will be pelagic/demersal otter trawled and have an MCS rating of 2.</p>

They assure standards particularly relating to food safety and no eggs laid under the Laid in Britain scheme have ever in its 17 year history been found to have salmonella. Spanish Onion Red Organic 500g
1
<p class="p1">To avoid weeping buckets when it comes to chopping time, follow these tips:&nbsp;</p>
<p class="p1">- Chill your onions in the fridge before slicing - the colder they are, the better&nbsp;</p>
<p class="p1">- Use a sharp knife - blunt knives burst more of those tear-inducing onion cells&nbsp;</p>
<p class="p1">- Slice under a trickle of water - it helps wash away the pongy vapours&nbsp;</p>
<p class="p1">- Wear swimming goggles&nbsp;</p>
<p class="p2">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="p1">Store your onions in the fridge, avoiding dampness, or in a cool dark larder.</p>

Binndings : 
Broccolini Bunch each
1
<p class="p1">This is a natural cross between broccoli and Chinese broccoli (gaai lan). It has a long slender stem topped with small flowering buds that are a cross between broccoli florets and an asparagus tip.</p>
<p class="p2">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="p1"><strong><em>What to look for</em></strong></p>
<p class="p1">Choose compact bud clusters with no yellow colouring or large open buds. Heads should be dark green or have a purple tinge (except for Romanesco, orange broccoli and broccoflower &ndash; they are a lighter, brighter green).</p>
<p class="p2">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="p1"><strong><em>Availability</em></strong></p>
<p class="p1">All Year.</p>
<p class="p2">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="p1"><strong><em>Store</em></strong></p>
<p class="p1">Refrigerate in plastic bags. Use promptly.</p>
<p class="p2">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="p1"><strong><em>How to prepare</em></strong></p>
<p class="p1">Trim stalks and divide heads into even sized portions. The stalks can be left attached to the florets. Alternatively, stalks can be removed, sliced finely and used in stir fries and soups; or julienned and used in coleslaw. Broccoli is usually eaten cooked &ndash; however, cook only until tender and still slightly crisp. Cook using methods such as steaming, microwaving and stir frying. To blanch, simply place portions in boiling water for 1-2 minutes, drain and cool under cold running water. Blanching improves taste, colour and texture.</p>
<p class="p2">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="p1"><strong><em>Ways to eat</em></strong></p>
<p class="p1">Broccoli is one of the most versatile vegetables. It can be served raw or lightly blanched and used in salads, pasta dishes, omelettes, quiches, soups and as a side dish.</p>
<p class="p2">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="p1"><strong><em>Cooking Methods</em></strong></p>
<p class="p1">Boil, steam, microwave, roast, stir fry.</p>

SQL : (2018-07-25 04:54:42)insert into `products` (`name`, `status`, `description`, `supplier_id`, `category_id`, `price`, `created_by`, `updated_at`, `created_at`) values (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?)
Binndings : 
Garlic Australian each
1
<p class="p1">Bulb made up of segments called cloves, covered by a papery shell. The most common varieties of garlic contain 10 cloves (or segments) with white skin. Other varieties have pink or purple skin and larger cloves. As a rule, the smaller the clove, the stronger the taste.&nbsp;</p>
<p class="p1">It is a member of the allium family that also includes onions, chives, shallots, spring onions and leeks.</p>
<p class="p2">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="p1"><strong><em>What to look for</em></strong></p>
<p class="p1">Look for firm well-shaped cloves. Buy in small amounts and break off the cloves only when needed. Garlic dries out once detached. bulb of garlic has had its roots trimmed, one at a time. Garlic is never labelled since it sheds its skin if a label is applied to it.</p>
<p class="p2">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="p1"><strong><em>Availability</em></strong></p>
<p class="p1">All year.</p>
<p class="p2">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="p1"><strong><em>Store</em></strong></p>
<p class="p1">Keep in a cool dry place away from the sunlight. Avoid placing in plastic bags, or storing in the refrigerator or everything in the refrigerator will end up tasting of garlic. Avoid storing next to ginger as ginger dehydrates garlic.</p>
<p class="p2">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="p1"><strong><em>How to prepare</em></strong></p>
<p class="p1">Separate cloves from bulbs, remove papery skin unless roasting when skin can be left on. Cut bulbs in half crosswise and brush with oil to roast. To remove skin, press the clove under the flat side of a knife and the skin will come off easily. Chop the garlic very finely or crush it with the side of a knife. Alternatively, use a garlic crusher.</p>
<p class="p2">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="p1"><strong><em>Ways to eat</em></strong></p>
<p class="p1">Garlic can be eaten raw or cooked. Raw garlic produces a strong, pungent flavour while cooking gives a more mellow flavour. The longer garlic is cooked, the milder and sweeter the flavour. It's usually used in small amounts, 2-3 cloves to a dish. Garlic burns easily, so take care when frying or saut&eacute;ing. It can be used in vegetable dishes, meats, soups, dips, stir fries, braises and stews. Add whole unpeeled cloves into a roasting pan with meat or vegetables. Cut a whole head in half horizontally and roast in a little olive oil. When cooked, serve as it is, or squeeze the roasted flesh out and serve on crostini or fresh bread.</p>
<p class="p2">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="p1"><strong><em>Cooking Methods</em></strong></p>
<p class="p1">Roast, braise, stew, stir fry.</p>
1

Farmers' Own
1
<p><span style="color: #39464e; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #eeeeee;">Farmers' Own' comes from a group of innovative Aussie dairy farmers that have come together with Woolworths to bring you this great tasting quality Milk.</span></p>
<h2 style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 28px; vertical-align: baseline; background: #eeeeee; font-family: 'Fresh Sans', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #39464e; line-height: 1.07143;">Our Background</h2>
<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline; background: #eeeeee; color: #39464e; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;">The Farmers Own initiative was started back in 2013 with Farmers from the Manning Valley in NSW. The brand began with a trial of just eight local stores within the Manning Valley and 12 Sydney stores in NSW. It's success saw the brand expand into VIC, QLD, WA, SA and NT, all the while building direct relationships with Farmers from key provincial areas within these states (Margaret River WA. Otways Regions VIC, Sunshine Coast Hinterland QLD and Barossa Mid North Region SA). In a challenging time for Australian Dairy Farmers, Farmers Own has been a good news story. Check out our packaging to see what our Farmers have to say!</p>
<h2 style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 28px; vertical-align: baseline; background: #eeeeee; font-family: 'Fresh Sans', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #39464e; line-height: 1.07143;">Our Deal</h2>
<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline; background: #eeeeee; color: #39464e; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;">We have direct relationships with our Farmers and not via a processor or a Co-op to ensure they are getting a good deal every time. Our goal is to pay our Farmers a good price for their milk that allows them to continue to produce quality milk. We pick up milk from their farms and transport directly to be processed so we know exactly where the milk comes from that goes into Farmers' Own milk. Our Farmers are engaged in the branding and feel a sense of belonging to the brand because it is their milk that goes into each bottle. We work with our farmers on sustainable and good animal husbandry practices and our farmers and families are proudly active in promoting Farmers' Own branded milk in their communities.</p>
<h2 style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 28px; vertical-align: baseline; background: #eeeeee; font-family: 'Fresh Sans', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #39464e; line-height: 1.07143;">Awards we've won!</h2>
<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline; background: #eeeeee; color: #39464e; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;">Since launching, Farmers&rsquo; Own has gone onto win a bunch of Awards within Australian Dairy and Food Competitions listed below:</p>
<p><a style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline; background: #eeeeee; color: #25861e; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;" name="ourdeal"></a><a style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline; background: #eeeeee; color: #25861e; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;" name="ourawards"></a></p>
